A new high school is set to open its doors in East London in 2018, which will alleviate the frustration caused by a shortage of schools. Steve Biko High School will open to hundreds of pupils when it takes over the premises of Grens Primary and Prep Schools between Muir and Lambert streets, along Oxford street in Southernwood.For the full story get a copy of the Dispatch or subscribe to our e-Edition for the complete newspaper with jobs, classifieds, crosswords, TV schedules and back editions 